### Jumper Wires

<figure class="figure">
  <img src="CURRENT/jumper.png">
</figure>

This is a jumper wire, which is used to make electrical connections between different points on a breadboard.
By placing each end of a jumper wire into a hole, you connect those two rows so current can flow between them.

### DIP Switch

<figure class="figure">
  <img src="CURRENT/dip.jpg">
</figure>

This is a DIP switch, which is a small set of on-off switches packaged together in one component.
Each tiny switch can open or close a circuit, allowing or stopping current from flowing.
Soon, you will use a DIP switch to manually turn individual LEDs on or off.

